<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,1338]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,322,1271,1297]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Comment</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Foldi &amp; Kozar" authorityYear="2007" box="[338,533,1272,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="christopherus">
<emphasis box="[338,533,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">E. christopherus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from the other species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[932,1064,1272,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[932,1064,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in South America in the characteristic arrangement of the dorsal spinose setae in 2 longitudinal medial bands and 9 transverse rows.
</paragraph>
